{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"52c6a5d9-2977-4494-be96-fffdecc33581","content":"It's a simple change. In your project file, just **remove** (or set to `false`) the `UseVSTest` property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n\n<!-- After -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- UseVSTest removed — Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the default -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Key things to know:**\n\n1. **MSTest.Sdk 3.4+** uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default**, so simply deleting `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` is enough.\n2. **Test execution** changes from `dotnet test` using VSTest to the new platform runner. `dotnet test` still works but routes through the new platform.\n3. **Command-line syntax** differs — e.g., filters use `--filter` with a slightly different syntax. Check any CI scripts.\n4. **VSTest-specific adapters/extensions** (e.g., custom `.runsettings` features) may need updating; the new platform uses its own extension model.\n\n**Verify** by running:\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nIf everything passes, you're done!","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cfe5c5ec-c645-46fd-b811-ec185539a04a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have relevant content about this migration. I'll answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":370,"requestId":"0858:1F3FEB:8495FD3:92B998F:69EABE3B"},"id":"2eb58c33-54f1-4137-909f-87cf5bc4f7aa","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:51:18.793Z","parentId":"20cc9039-8160-4589-ad18-97421b115cbb"}
